<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="ceil" id="ceil">ceil</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntaxe :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">ceil</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">double</span> nb<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
La fonction <code>ceil()</code> renvoie le plus petit entier non-inférieur à <code>nb</code>.
</p>

<p>
Par exemple :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">     y <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="nu16">6.04</span><span class="sy4">;</span>
     x <span class="sy1">=</span> <span class="kw3">ceil</span><span class="br0">&#40;</span>y<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
après ce morceau de code, x vaut 7.0.
</p>

<p>
Le C++ fournit également les formes surchargée suivantes :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">ceil</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">float</span> nb<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// identique à ceilf() en C99</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">ceil</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> nb<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// identique à ceill() en C99</span></pre>
<p>
Sujets connexes : <a href="floor" class="wikilink1" title="fr:numeric:c:floor">floor</a>, <a href="fmod" class="wikilink1" title="fr:numeric:c:fmod">fmod</a>
</p>

